The paper discusses the use of massive MIMO systems with uniform planar arrays, which are commonly used in wireless communication networks. The focus is on improving channel state information accuracy, which is a key aspect of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of feedback information from users to base stations, which is a common topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of variable-rate CSI quantization schemes is also discussed, which is a topic in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of beamforming techniques, which are commonly used in antenna arrays and signal processing (cs.AR).
